'''莫維勒洞穴'''（{{Lang-ro|Peștera Movile}}）是一個位於[[羅馬尼亞|羅馬尼亞]][[康斯坦察縣|康斯坦察縣]][[曼加利亞|曼加利亞]]市郊，距[[黑海|黑海]]海岸不到數公里的自然封閉岩洞，於1986年被克里斯蒂安·拉斯庫（Cristian Lascu）發現<ref name=FoxSkelly2015>{{cite news |last1=Fox-Skelly |first1=Jasmin |title=The bizarre beasts living in Romania's poison cave |url=http://www.bbc.com/earth/story/20150904-the-bizarre-beasts-living-in-romanias-poison-cave |work=BBC Earth |date=4 September 2015 |accessdate=2021-02-01 |archive-date=2021-02-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210221135025/http://www.bbc.com/earth/story/20150904-the-bizarre-beasts-living-in-romanias-poison-cave |dead-url=no }}</ref>。該洞以獨特的[[地下水|地下水]]生態系統聞名，其大氣富含[[硫化氫|硫化氫]]和二氧化碳，但氧含量極低。在過去的550萬年中，莫維勒洞穴一直未受外界干擾，居住在其中的生物已完全捨棄[[光合作用|光合作用]]，僅靠[[化能合成|化能合成]]維生<ref name=FoxSkelly2015/>，也是世上唯一一個完全依賴化能合成的生態系統<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://caves.org/pub/journal/NSS%20Bulletin/Vol%2057%20num%202.pdf|title=A Subterranean Chemoautotrophically Based Ecostsyem|format=pdf|journal=The NSS Bulletin|volume=57|issue=2|date=1995-12|accessdate=2021-02-01|page=91|publisher=National Speleological Society|issn=0146-9517|author1=Serban M. Sarbu|author2=Thomas C. Kane|editor=Andrew J. Flurkey|location=USA|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103214051/https://caves.org/pub/journal/NSS%20Bulletin/Vol%2057%20num%202.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Stand">{{cite web|url=https://www.thestandnews.com/cosmos/歐洲密封-550-萬年洞穴發現全新無色蜈蚣-被命名為-洞穴之王|title=歐洲密封 550 萬年洞穴 發現全新無色素有毒蜈蚣 命名為「洞穴之王」|publisher=[[立場新聞|立場新聞]]|date=2020-12-21|accessdate=2020-02-01|archive-date=2021-02-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210216150038/https://www.thestandnews.com/cosmos/%E6%AD%90%E6%B4%B2%E5%AF%86%E5%B0%81-550-%E8%90%AC%E5%B9%B4%E6%B4%9E%E7%A9%B4%E7%99%BC%E7%8F%BE%E5%85%A8%E6%96%B0%E7%84%A1%E8%89%B2%E8%9C%88%E8%9A%A3-%E8%A2%AB%E5%91%BD%E5%90%8D%E7%82%BA-%E6%B4%9E%E7%A9%B4%E4%B9%8B%E7%8E%8B/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 大氣環境 ==
莫維勒洞穴的大氣環境與外界完全不同，其氧氣含量僅為外界的三分之一至一半（洞穴內的O<sub>2</sub>含量為7%－10%，而大氣中的O<sub>2</sub>則為21%），屬{{link-en|缺氧 (環境)|Hypoxia (environmental)|缺氧環境}}<ref name="KumaresanWischer2014"/>。相比之下，該洞的二氧化碳濃度卻比外界大氣多100倍（大氣的CO<sub>2</sub>濃度僅有0.04%，洞穴內的CO<sub>2</sub>濃度則為2%－3.5%）。莫維勒洞穴還含有1%－2%的甲烷（CH<sub>4</sub>），其空氣和水中也含有高濃度的[[硫化氫|硫化氫]]（H<sub>2</sub>S）和氨（NH<sub>3</sub>）<ref name="KumaresanWischer2014">{{cite journal |last1=Kumaresan |first1=Deepak |last2=Wischer |first2=Daniela |last3=Stephenson |first3=Jason |last4=Hillebrand-Voiculescu |first4=Alexandra |last5=Murrell |first5=J. Colin |title=Microbiology of Movile Cave—A Chemolithoautotrophic Ecosystem |journal=Geomicrobiology Journal |date=16 March 2014 |volume=31 |issue=3 |pages=186–193 |doi=10.1080/01490451.2013.839764 }}</ref>。

== 生態 ==
[[File:Centopéia_Cryptops_speleorex.png|thumb]]
在莫維勒洞穴內發現的動物物種已知有51個<ref name=Vahtera2020/>，包括[[蚂蟥|蚂蟥]]、蜘蛛、[[擬蠍目|擬蠍]]<ref name=Nag2017 />、{{link-en|潮蟲亞目|Woodlouse|潮蟲}}<ref>Karen Graham: [http://www.digitaljournal.com/science/movile-cave-in-romania-has-an-ecosystem-unlike-any-other-on-earth/article/466274 Movile Cave in Romania has an ecosystem unlike any other on Earth] {{Wayback|url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/science/movile-cave-in-romania-has-an-ecosystem-unlike-any-other-on-earth/article/466274 |date=20210226215744 }}. In: DigitalJournal. 25 May 2016. Source: Science</ref>、蜈蚣<ref name=Vahtera2020>Varpu Vahtera, Pavel Stoev, Nesrine Akkari: [https://zookeys.pensoft.net/article/58537/element/8/5352 Five million years in the darkness: A new troglomorphic species of ''Cryptops'' Leach, 1814 (Chilopoda, Scolopendromorpha) from Movile Cave, Romania] {{Wayback|url=https://zookeys.pensoft.net/article/58537/element/8/5352 |date=20210204153124 }}. On: [[ZooKeys|ZooKeys]] 1004: pp 1-26. [[doi:10.3897/zookeys.1004.58537|doi:10.3897/zookeys.1004.58537]] (16 December 2020). See also:
* David Nield: [https://www.sciencealert.com/this-toxic-underground-ecosystem-is-like-nothing-else-on-earth-today-and-we-just-found-its-largest-inhabitant Meet The 'King' of a Toxic Underground Ecosystem Unlike Anywhere Else on Earth] {{Wayback|url=https://www.sciencealert.com/this-toxic-underground-ecosystem-is-like-nothing-else-on-earth-today-and-we-just-found-its-largest-inhabitant |date=20210215180951 }}. On: science<sup>alert</sup>. 19 December 2020. About ''{{link-ru|Cryptops speleorex|Cryptops speleorex}}'', the cave dwelling sister species of ''{{link-en|Cryptops hortensis|Cryptops hortensis|C. hortensis}}'', {{link-en|盲蜈蚣科|Cryptopidae|Cryptopidae}}

* [https://scitechdaily.com/new-centipede-discovered-on-top-of-food-chain-in-hellish-ecosystem-of-a-sulfur-soaked-romanian-cave/ New Centipede Discovered on Top of Food Chain in Hellish Ecosystem of a Sulfur-Soaked Romanian Cave] {{Wayback|url=https://scitechdaily.com/new-centipede-discovered-on-top-of-food-chain-in-hellish-ecosystem-of-a-sulfur-soaked-romanian-cave/ |date=20210415014023 }}. On: SciTechDaily. December 16, 2020</ref>、[[蠍蝽科|水蠍]]和蝸牛等<ref name=Falniowski2008 />。在這51個物種中，有35個是該洞穴才有的[[特有種|特有種]]<ref name=Vahtera2020/>。在莫維勒洞穴內，食物鏈的能量來源起始於化能合成作用，[[厭氧甲烷氧化|甲烷氧化菌]]和{{link-en|微生物代謝|Microbial metabolism|硫氧化菌}}是[[食物鏈|食物鏈]]的最底層生物，他們靠[[化能合成|化能合成]]維生，同時也釋出諸如[[真菌|真菌]]或其他細菌所需的養分。這些菌類會在洞穴壁以及湖泊和池塘的表面形成[[微生物席|微生物席]]，[[植食性動物|植食性動物]]會以這些微生物維生，然後肉食性動物便會掠食牠們<ref>{{cite web |title=Microbial food webs in Movile Cave |url=https://gtr.ukri.org/projects?ref=NE%2FG017956%2F1 |website=UK Research and Innovation |access-date=2021-02-01 |archive-date=2020-10-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201009130757/https://gtr.ukri.org/projects?ref=NE%2FG017956%2F1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

居住在莫維勒洞穴內，{{link-en|蠍蝽屬|Nepa (insect)}}之一的''Nepa anophthalma''（可譯作「缺眼水蠍」）是世上唯一已知存在的{{link-en|穴居動物|Stygofauna|穴居性}}水蠍<ref name=Decu1994>{{cite journal |last1=Decu |first1=Vasile |last2=Gruia |first2=Magdalena |last3=Keffer |first3=S. L. |last4=Sarbu |first4=Serban Mircea |title=Stygobiotic Waterscorpion, Nepa anophthalma, n. sp. (Heteroptera: Nepidae), from a Sulfurous Cave in Romania |journal=Annals of the Entomological Society of America |date=1 November 1994 |volume=87 |issue=6 |pages=755–761 |doi=10.1093/aesa/87.6.755 }}</ref>。{{link-ru|Cryptops speleorex|Cryptops speleorex|''Cryptops speleorex''}}（可譯作「洞穴大王{{link-en|盲蜈蚣科|Cryptopidae|盲蜈蚣}}」）則是該洞穴迄今已知的最大動物，其身上完全沒有色素，表面呈鮮黃色<ref name="Stand"/>，且最初被鑑定為''Cryptops anomalans''（可譯作「異形盲蜈蚣」），直至2020年才有科學家因形態與分子上的差異將其劃為新種<ref name=Vahtera2020/>。雖然研究人員發現莫維勒洞穴在550萬年前已有生物存在，但各物種遷入的時間可能不同，例如有以[[mtDNA|mtDNA]]為[[分子鐘|分子鐘]]的研究結果顯示洞穴內特有種''Heleobia dobrogica''（可譯作「[[多瑙河|多瑙河]]{{link-en|湖泊螺屬|Heleobia|湖泊螺}}」）和洞穴外同屬物種分家的時間約在200多萬年前，與[[第四紀冰河時期|歐洲冰河期]]開始的時間略顯吻合，因此該物種的形成可能與其祖先在冰期初期遷入相對溫暖的洞穴中有關<ref name=FoxSkelly2015 /><ref name=Nag2017>{{cite news |last1=Nag |first1=Oishimaya Sen |title=Movile Cave - An Oddity Of Romania |url=https://www.worldatlas.com/articles/movile-cave-an-oddity-of-romania.html |work=WorldAtlas |date=25 April 2017 |accessdate=2021-02-01 |archive-date=2018-07-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180706075621/https://www.worldatlas.com/articles/movile-cave-an-oddity-of-romania.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Falniowski2008>Andrzej Falniowski, Magdalena Szarowska, Ioan Sirbu, Alexandra Hillebrand, Mihai Baciu: [https://www.mapress.com/mr/content/v28/2008f/n3p170.htm ''Heleobia dobrogica'' (Grossu & Negrea, 1989)(Gastropoda: Rissooidea: Cochliopidae) and the estimated time of its isolation in a continental analogue of hydrothermal vents] {{Wayback|url=https://www.mapress.com/mr/content/v28/2008f/n3p170.htm |date=20210310190510 }}. In: Molluscan Research 28(3): pp 165-170. 22 Dec 2008. ISSN 1323-5818</ref>。

